# Component Conventions

## Directory Layout
```
components/
  ui/           ← shadcn/ui primitives (Button, Input, Dialog, etc.) — do not modify unless upgrading
  admin/        ← Admin dashboard-specific components
  app/          ← Shared app-wide components
    public/     ← Public-facing section components
  layouts/      ← Layout wrappers
  home/         ← Home page sections
  mail/         ← Email templates (@react-email)
  pdf/          ← PDF generation
  profile/      ← User profile components
  footer/       ← Footer components
```

## Layout Components
Use the appropriate layout wrapper from `components/layouts/`:
- `PublicLayout` — public-facing pages with header/footer
- `AdminLayout` — admin dashboard shell
- `SectionLayout` — consistent section padding/max-width
- `PublicDetailsLayout` — detail page with back navigation
- `ComponentLayout` — component showcase pages

## shadcn/ui Usage
Always import base UI primitives from `@/components/ui/`:
```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogHeader } from "@/components/ui/dialog";
```

Do **not** install new Radix primitives directly — add them as shadcn components to `components/ui/` instead.

## Client vs Server Components
- Default to **Server Components** in `app/` pages
- Add `"use client"` only when the component uses: `useState`, `useEffect`, event handlers, browser APIs, or React Query hooks
- Keep data-fetching logic in server components or React Query hooks; keep UI interactivity in client components

## Naming
- Files: `PascalCase` with a descriptive suffix — `ProductItemComponent.tsx`, `DashboardCardComponent.tsx`
- Component function: matches the file name
```tsx
// File: components/app/public/ProductItemComponent.tsx
export default function ProductItemComponent({ ... }) { ... }
```

## Props
- Always define a TypeScript interface or type for props
- Import shared types from `@/types/` rather than re-defining inline

```tsx
import { Product } from "@/types/dashboard/products";

interface Props {
  product: Product;
  onClick?: () => void;
}

export default function ProductItemComponent({ product, onClick }: Props) { ... }
```

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` to conditionally merge class names:
```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";
<div className={cn("base-classes", isActive && "active-class")} />
```

## Icons
Use `lucide-react` for icons:
```tsx
import { ShoppingCart, ChevronRight } from "lucide-react";
```
